      "type": "Term",
      "front": "impressment",
      "back": "The Royal Navy resumed the practice of impressment. Jefferson hoped it would lead Europeans to stop their interference with American shipping and also reduce the occasion for impressment. But the British continued to attack American vessels and, with their navy hard-pressed for manpower, stepped up the impressment of American sailors.",
