      "chapterId": "chapter8",
      "type": "Term",
      "front": "Judith Sargent Murray",
      "back": "Judith Sargent Murray, one of the era's most accomplished American women, wrote essays for the Massachusetts Magazine under the pen name \"The Gleaner.\" Murray's father, a prosperous Massachusetts merchant, had taken an enlightened view of his daughter's education.",
      "hint": "Judith Sargent Murray, one of the era's most accomplished American women, wrote essays for the Massachusetts Magazine under the pen name \"The Gleaner.\" Murray's father, a prosperous Massachusetts merchant, had taken an enlightened view of his daughter's education.",
