      "chapterId": "chapter8",
      "type": "Term",
      "front": "Hamilton's Program",
      "back": "Hamilton's program had five parts. The third part of Hamilton's program called for the creation of a Bank of the United States, modeled on the Bank of England, to serve as the nation's main financial agent. At first, opposition to Hamilton's program arose almost entirely from the South, the region that had the least interest in manufacturing development and the least diversified economy.",
