      "id": "chapter8-fc-032",
      "chapterId": "chapter8",
      "type": "Term",
      "front": "The Emergence of Opposition",
      "back": "Political divisions first surfaced over the financial plan developed by Hamilton in 1790 and 1791. His immediate aims were to establish the nation's financial stability, bring to the government's support the country's most powerful financial interests, and encourage economic development. His long-term goal was to make the United States a major commercial and military power.",
      "hint": "Political divisions first surfaced over the financial plan developed by Hamilton in 1790 and 1791.",
